 <H1>Decision Lists and ILP</H1> 
 <P><UL>
<LI><H2>FOCL (and FOIL, etc.) designed for binary classification problems
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>learn clauses that cover all positive an no negatives
</UL></UL><UL>
<LI><H2>When there are n  classes, run learner n  times
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>treat examples of each class in turn as positives
<LI>treat examples of other classes as negative
</UL></UL><UL>
<LI><H2>Classification issues
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>When clauses from more than one class are satisfied
<LI>When no clause is satisfied
</UL></UL><UL>
<LI><H2>Decision Lists
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>Ordered set of clauses
<LI>Default clause if no clause matches
</UL></UL><UL>
<LI><H2>Better Safe Than Sorry (Provost & Buchanan)</H2>
</UL></P>
<P></P> 
